categories.name: General
categories.description: Create topics here that don’t fit into any other existing category.

categories.name: Documentation
categories.description: Official documentation for how to use Discourse, install and configure sites, develop plugins and themes, and troubleshoot common issues. Includes topics for tutorials, how-tos, general reference and troubleshooting.

categories.name: Community wiki
categories.description: This wiki includes guides, tips, and examples written by members of the Discourse community. All content is created and edited by users of Trust Level 2 and above, and is open to new community contributions.

categories.name: Announcements
categories.description: Important News and Updates from Discourse

categories.name: Support
categories.description: The category for general support questions on using your Discourse site.

categories.name: Bug
categories.description: A bug report means something is broken, preventing normal/typical use of Discourse. Do be sure to search prior to submitting bugs. Include repro steps, and only describe one bug per topic please.

categories.name: UX
categories.description: Discussion about the user interface of Discourse and how features are presented (including language and UI elements).

categories.name: Feature
categories.description: Discussion about existing Discourse features, how they can be improved or enhanced, and how proposed new features could work.

categories.name: Data & reporting
categories.description: This is the category for everything related to Discourse data and reporting. Here, you can discuss dashboard reports, custom badge queries, data-explorer queries and any other analytic add-ons.

categories.name: SSO
categories.description: For queries specifically about SSO (single sign-on) and login using third-party providers (Google, Facebook, GitHub etc). See the official documentation on DiscourseConnect SSO.

categories.name: Community
categories.description: A great platform doesn’t guarantee success. Community building is a science. This category is for discussions about launching, building, growing and managing a thriving community.

categories.name: Dev
categories.description: The category for all things Discourse Development. Building a customization for yourself or the community? Then this is the category for you!

categories.name: Marketplace
categories.description: This is your hub for all Discourse-related commerce: jobs, gigs, plugins, themes, hosting, and more.

categories.name: Plugin
categories.description: A directory of Discourse plugins, both official and third-party.

categories.name: Theme
categories.description: Themes are expansive customizations that change multiple elements of the style of your forum design, and often also include additional front-end features.

categories.name: Theme component
categories.description: Theme components are customizations that change surface elements of your forum design, or add extra front-end features.

categories.name: Installation
categories.description: Getting Discourse up and running, keeping it going, updating, and any other general sysadmin maintenance.

categories.name: Migration
categories.description: You want to migrate your community to Discourse? Awesome! This is the category where you can ask questions, get help, and document your Discourse migration journey.

categories.name: Releases
categories.description: Outlining each official release of Discourse, and plans for future releases.

categories.name: Site feedback
categories.description: Discussion about meta.discourse.org itself - the organization of this forum, how it works, and how we can improve this site.

categories.name: Praise
categories.description: Have something nice to say about Discourse? We would love to hear it

categories.name: IEEE Summer of Code 2025
categories.description: Discussion about Discourse contributions on the IEEE Summer of Code 2025.
